 {"id":"franken_networkx-b2x7","title":"parity: Graph and DiGraph degree() should be callable","description":"Graph.degree() and DiGraph.degree() currently expose non-callable view objects, so every callable form fails: list(G.degree()), G.degree('a'), and G.degree('a', weight='weight') all raise TypeError in FrankenNetworkX while upstream NetworkX supports them and returns iterator/scalar degree results. Match the upstream callable degree() contract on Graph and DiGraph.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T08:26:26.849615920Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T08:27:59.192133425Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
