 {"id":"franken_networkx-b7fx","title":"parity: DiGraph and MultiDiGraph should support reverse(copy=...)","description":"DiGraph.reverse() and MultiDiGraph.reverse() currently reject the copy keyword entirely with TypeError, while upstream NetworkX exposes reverse(copy=True) and reverse(copy=False). Match the upstream reverse(copy=...) signature on the core directed graph classes; copy=False should be routed through the existing live-view semantics work, while copy=True should preserve the current copied-reverse behavior.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T08:07:59.266076503Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T08:09:45.427816153Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
